  "title": "Senior/System Control Engineer - Up to $5300",
  "description": "<p><strong>Job Description:</strong></p><p>· Lead the design, development, and integration of marine electrical and automation systems.</p><p>· Prepare, review, and approve electrical drawings, wiring diagrams, and schematics.</p><p>· Develop and implement PLC programs, HMI interfaces, and control logic.</p><p>· Configure and optimize VFDs, motor controllers, and motion control systems.</p><p>· Oversee system integration, testing, and troubleshooting across project phases.</p><p>· Manage and support FAT, SAT, and vessel commissioning activities.</p><p>· Ensure compliance with marine class societies (DNV, ABS, BV, etc.) and safety regulations.</p><p>· Mentor junior engineers and contribute to technical training within the team.</p><p>· Ad-hoc tasks as assigned.</p><p><strong>Job Requirements:</strong></p><p>· Degree in Electrical Engineering, Mechatronics, Automation, or related field.</p><p>· 4–8 years of experience in system control and industrial automation.</p><p>· Proven expertise with PLC programming, motion control, and electrical system design.</p><p>· Strong project execution, leadership, and mentoring skills.</p><p>· Experience with marine or offshore electrical systems is a strong advantage.</p><p>· Familiarity with marine classification and regulatory standards is a strong advantage.<br /><br /><br /><strong>Interested and suitable candidate kindly click quick apply. Resume will be forwarded to Stepfan Soon Yit</strong></p><p><strong>We regret that only suitable candidate will be notified.</strong></p><p><strong>GEMS Recruit/EA License : 23C1459</strong></p><p><strong>EA Personnel No : R24120893 (Stepfan Soon Yit)</strong></p>",
